pokračovaní minulého příspěvku:

So the 'iron lines' on diagrams of the boat shape and the lines of plastic
tape in photo graphs are only an interpretation based on 'results' from a
pseudo-scientific 'instrument'. They have not been able to be reproduced or
verified by any reputable scientific survey technique, including standard
metal detection equipment. This includes the highly sophisticated types of
magnetometer used by mining companies (see later). (* Even Baumgardner, to his
later embarrassment, was initially taken in by the false claims attributed to
this 'instrument'. Fasold still promotes its virtues and cries 'foul' when
these 'home truths' are pointed out, yet if it were what he claims then every
mining company and fortune seeker would own and operate one and be making
hordes of money! No mining company uses anything like it.)

